    <!-- carte DRC Executive presentation -->
    <div class="carte-executive animate-scroll">
      
       <h2><img class="logo_home_page" src="images/logo/logo1_printing.jpg" alt="Jeunesse 243"> 
                   <br> Employment • Training
<br> Entrepreneurship
                    </h2>
  <div class="apropos1ligne1">                   
  <p>
  <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> is the <strong>first professional social network</strong> dedicated to
  <strong>employment</strong>, <strong>training</strong>, and <strong>entrepreneurship</strong> for
  <strong>young Congolese people</strong> aged <strong>18 to 40</strong>, in the <strong>DRC</strong> and across the
  <strong>diaspora</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  The platform aims to <strong>connect</strong> <strong>talents</strong>,
  <strong>recruiters</strong>, <strong>job seekers</strong>, <strong>companies</strong>,
  <strong>institutions</strong>, <strong>training providers</strong>, and
  <strong>investors</strong>, in order to structure a
  <strong>digital ecosystem of opportunities</strong> serving the
  <strong>Congolese youth</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  In this context, <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> seeks to connect young people to
  <strong>employment</strong>, <strong>subcontracting</strong>, and <strong>training</strong>
  opportunities arising both from the <strong>national economic fabric</strong>,
  notably through <strong>companies that are members of FEC</strong>
  (<strong>Federation of Enterprises of the Congo</strong>), and from
  <strong>international strategic investments</strong>, particularly those stemming from the
  <strong>global strategic partnership</strong> between the <strong>DRC</strong> and the
  <strong>United States</strong>, as well as <strong>investments from Qatar</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  Furthermore, in a context marked by the <strong>recent partnership</strong> concluded between
  <strong>Cisco</strong>, <strong>Cybastion</strong>, and the <strong>Ministry of Youth</strong>, which provides for the
  <strong>training of 250,000 young Congolese</strong> over a period of <strong>five years</strong>,
  <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> intends to play the role of a <strong>relay platform</strong>.
</p>

<p>
  The objective is to facilitate the <strong>identification</strong>,
  <strong>guidance</strong>, and <strong>connection</strong> of young people with these
  <strong>structured training programs</strong>, in order to strengthen their
  <strong>employability</strong>, their <strong>professional qualifications</strong>, and their
  <strong>integration</strong> into <strong>local</strong> and
  <strong>international value chains</strong>.
</p>

  <h2><strong> <i class="fa fa-eye"></i> VISION</strong></h2>
  <p>
    To make Congolese youth a central economic actor—skilled, connected, and value-creating—capable of meeting the needs of both local and international markets.
  </p>

  <h2><strong><i class="fa fa-bullseye"></i> MISSION</strong></h2>
  <ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Facilitate access to employment</strong> by enabling <strong>companies</strong> and
    <strong>recruiters</strong> to publish <strong>job opportunities</strong>, allowing
    <strong>job seekers</strong> to <strong>apply in one click</strong>, and by organizing
    <strong>job fairs</strong>, <strong>job dating sessions</strong>, and
    <strong>professional immersion programs</strong>.
  </li>
  <li>
    Promote <strong>vocational</strong> and <strong>professional training</strong>
  </li>
  <li>
    Encourage <strong>youth entrepreneurship</strong>
  </li>
  <li>
    Structure a <strong>reliable Congolese professional network</strong>
  </li>
  <li>
    Enhance and promote <strong>local</strong> and <strong>diaspora skills</strong>
  </li>
</ul>


  </div>
  
  
