   <!-- Ecosystem presentation card -->
<div class="carte-executive animate-scroll">
  <h2><i class="fa fa-network-wired"></i> ECOSYSTEM:
  <br>FEC & Economic Partnerships</h2>

  <p style="font-size:14px;">
    <em>Connecting Congolese youth to the national economic fabric and strategic partnerships.</em>
  </p>

  <div class="apropos1ligne1"> 

    <p>
      <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> is part of a collaborative dynamic with
      national and international economic actors, with the aim of fostering
      sustainable professional integration and strengthening youth participation
      in the economic development of the
      <strong>Democratic Republic of the Congo</strong>.
    </p>

    <p>
      To this end, the platform intends to work in synergy with the
      <strong>Federation of Enterprises of the Congo (FEC)</strong>,
      a key pillar of the Congolese private sector, with the objective of connecting young talents
      to businesses, whether they are FEC member companies or other structured economic actors.
      <br>This collaboration aims to facilitate access to <strong>job opportunities</strong>,
      <strong>internships</strong>, <strong>professional assignments</strong> and
      <strong>subcontracting opportunities</strong> generated by the national economic fabric.
    </p>

    <p>
      Furthermore, <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> positions itself as a bridge platform
      between Congolese youth and
      <strong>strategic economic partnerships</strong>, particularly those arising from the
      <strong>"Global Strategic Partnership"</strong> between the <strong>DRC</strong> and the
      <strong>United States</strong>, as well as investments from <strong>Qatar</strong>.
      <br>These dynamics offer significant prospects in terms of job creation,
      skills development and the structuring of value chains.
    </p>

    <p>
      Within this framework, <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> is also part of a broader
      ecosystem of <strong>complementary platforms</strong>, working to
      <strong>connect</strong> <strong>talents, job seekers, recruiters, businesses, the diaspora</strong>
      and <strong>investors</strong>, in support of the economic development of the DRC.
    </p>

    <p>
      Through this network of partnerships, <strong>Jeunesse 243</strong> aims to play
      a <strong>facilitating economic role</strong>, by bringing together businesses,
      investors, institutions and young talents, within a logic of
      complementarity, value creation and inclusive development.
    </p>

  </div>
</div>
<!-- END Ecosystem card -->

